hooks.prompt:
A git commit is about to run in the ShopStack repo. Review the staged changes by running `git diff --cached`, applying the standards in .claude/agents/code-structure-reviewer.md — enforcing these five pillars in priority order: (1) naming & cohesion, (2) lint (flake8 ruleset: F401, F841, F811, F821, C901, E/W), (3) docstyle, (4) import order, (5) PEP8 spacing. Do NOT gate on multi-tenancy safety, ORM correctness, transactional integrity, or test coverage — those are out of scope for this hook. Then return your decision as JSON on stdout in this exact shape — and nothing else after the JSON:

If the verdict is CHANGES_REQUIRED, output:
{"hookSpecificOutput":{"hookEventName":"PreToolUse","permissionDecision":"deny","permissionDecisionReason":"<one-paragraph summary of blockers + actionable fixes>"}}

Otherwise (APPROVED or APPROVED_WITH_NITS), output:
{"hookSpecificOutput":{"hookEventName":"PreToolUse","permissionDecision":"allow"},"systemMessage":"<one-line review summary>"}

Tool input that triggered this hook: $ARGUMENTS
